<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 03 at 5:26PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southeastern Pulaski, southwestern Floyd and Carroll Counties through
600 PM EDT...
At 526 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dugspur, or 7 miles northeast of Hillsville, moving southwest at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hillsville...
Indian Valley...
Fancy Gap...
Willis...
Dugspur...
Sylvatus...
and Gladesboro.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
